CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 9, 1941, pg. 16, reads: "Fighting for City Sandlot Baseball Title - Pictured above is one of the city's outstanding baseball teams, the Pittsburgh Monarchs who is now in thick of the fight for the Municipal baseball title."
TitMainTitle: Pittsburgh Monarchs sandlot baseball team, including a few players wearing Homestead Stars jerseys, posed on Homewood Brushton Field
